		<legis-type>A BILL</legis-type>
		<official-title>To prohibit the further extension or establishment of
		  national monuments in Montana, except by express authorization of Congress, and
		  for other purposes.</official-title>
	</form>
	<legis-body id="H188ADEDB925F4C81BB478DBA30B85C69" style="OLC">
		<section id="HA53694553620499EA69ED4D4CAA06037" section-type="section-one">
      <enum>1.</enum>
      <header>Short title</header>
      <text display-inline="no-display-inline">This Act may be cited as the
			 <quote>
          <short-title>Montana Land Sovereignty
			 Act</short-title>
        </quote>.</text>
		</section>
    <section id="H678C371B05314983B0D1D8BD1F998245">
      <enum>2.</enum>
      <header>Prohibition on
			 new national monuments in montana without congressional approval</header>
      <text display-inline="no-display-inline">This proviso of the last sentence of the
			 first section of the <cato:entity xmlns:cato="http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml" entity-type="law-citation">
          <cato:entity-ref entity-type="act" value="Grand Teton National Park Act" official-title="true">Act of September 14, 1950</cato:entity-ref> (<cato:entity-ref entity-type="statute-at-large" value="statute-at-large/64/849">64 Stat. 849, chapter 950</cato:entity-ref>; <cato:entity-ref entity-type="uscode" value="usc/16/431a">16
			 U.S.C. 431a</cato:entity-ref>)</cato:entity>, is amended by inserting <quote>or Montana</quote> after
			 <quote>Wyoming</quote>.</text>
		</section>
